          </a>
  </figure>
  <div class="post__summary">
    <p>Traveling is really, really great. I mean, I know that’s not exactly newsworthy, but bear with me for a minute. I guess what I mean is that, especially since I started working at home, where I spend lots of long hours in concentration and quiet, every time I go away, I feel thirsty somehow &#8211; like an old, crusty sponge, waiting to soak up something, anything, a new sight or smell or taste. And it feels so good to drink it all in, the way you’d do with a glass of water, in one enormous gulp, on a humid day. All that drinking in and soaking up, all that traveling, so good. But then, after a while, coming home is&hellip;</p>
    <a href="https://orangette.net/2008/04/the-way-a-cloud-would/" class="post-more">Read more</a>
  </div>
</article>
